# Agent Interaction Conventions

These rules govern how the assistant communicates and delivers changes. They do
not cover code style (see `clean-code`), scope discipline (see
`anti-overengineering`), or honesty and verification (see `anti-sycophancy`).

## Communication
- Do not apologize.
- Do not add feedback about your own understanding in code or documentation.
- Do not summarize the changes you made unless the user asks.
- Do not show or discuss the current implementation unless the user asks.
- Do not ask the user to confirm information already present in the context.
- Do not ask the user to verify implementations that are visible in the context.

## Delivering Edits
- Apply all edits to a single file in one pass; do not make several incremental
  passes over the same file.
- When a change spans multiple files, work through them one file at a time so
  each file's diff is reviewable on its own.
- Do not propose whitespace-only changes.
- Match the existing coding style of the file and the surrounding project.
